The paper deals with scene decomposition and representation using deep learning techniques, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the use of unsupervised learning to achieve this goal, which falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper uses a recurrent attention network, which is a common technique in neural networks (cs.NE). Finally, the paper discusses the semantic representation of objects, which is a topic in natural language processing (cs.CL).
